{"parentUuid":"3ee7abce-6d62-4e76-a7ce-135b4b8ed89a","isSidechain":false,"type":"system","subtype":"turn_duration","durationMs":77377,"timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:22:03.194Z","uuid":"654ed291-acae-4f48-9da0-a8e33a09a722","isMeta":false,"userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"654ed291-acae-4f48-9da0-a8e33a09a722","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"e511017c-10f2-48ae-a4ee-fd8e203bf2c9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"<task-notification>\n<task-id>ac8528320e1f3a037</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>REDACTED</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/ac8528320e1f3a037.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Code review PR 983 final\" completed</summary>\n<result>The adopt step creates slot data directly without running through `CODE_SLOT_SCHEMA`. The schema only does `vol.Optional` checks and `cv.string`/`cv.boolean` coercion, so the hardcoded values (`CONF_NAME: f\"Slot {slot}\"`, `CONF_PIN: str(code)`, `CONF_ENABLED: True`) already satisfy the schema. This is fine -- the values are controlled, not user-provided.\n\nNow let me verify the adopt step handles the case where `self.data` already has `CONF_SLOTS` from a previous flow step (it shouldn't, since adopt happens before choose_path, but let's verify the flow order).\n\nThe flow is: `user` -> `lock_reset` -> `lock_reset_adopt` -> `choose_path` -> `ui`/`yaml`. So `CONF_SLOTS` wouldn't be set yet from user input. The `setdefault` at line 304 is correct.\n\nHowever, there's a subtle issue. If the user chooses \"adopt\" and then goes to the \"ui\" path, the UI path at line 386 creates `self.slots_to_configure = list(range(start, start + num_slots))`. Then in `async_step_code_slot` at line 412, it does `self.data.setdefault(CONF_SLOTS, {})`. If adopted slots overlap with the UI-configured range, they'd be overwritten at line 434. This is actually correct behavior -- the user is explicitly configuring those slots in the UI.\n\nBut wait -- if the user goes through the \"yaml\" path, line 468 does `self.data[CONF_SLOTS] = slots`, which completely replaces any adopted slots. The test `test_lock_reset_readable_codes_adopt` confirms this works because it submits the adopted slots in the YAML step. So the user must include adopted slots in their YAML submission or they'll be lost. This seems like intended behavior since the YAML path gives full control.\n\nI have completed my review. Let me summarize.\n\n---\n\n## Code Review: PR #983 (feat/lock-reset-step)\n\n**Reviewing:** `git diff main...feat/lock-reset-step` across 4 changed files:\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/config_flow.py`\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/strings.json`\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/translations/en.json`\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/tests/test_config_flow.py`\n\n### No high-confidence issues found (confidence >= 80)\n\nThe code is well-structured and handles edge cases carefully. Here is what I verified:\n\n**Correctness:**\n- `BaseLock` dataclass constructor call with 5 positional args matches the field order (`hass, dev_reg, ent_reg, lock_config_entry, lock`).\n- `async_internal_clear_usercode(slot, source=\"direct\")` matches the method signature.\n- `is` identity comparisons against `SlotCode.EMPTY` and `SlotCode.UNKNOWN` are consistent with the rest of the codebase (these are `StrEnum` singletons).\n- The `_execute_rate_limited` path inside `async_internal_clear_usercode` accesses `self.coordinator` but guards it with a truthiness check, so the `None` default on the temporary lock instance is safe.\n- `int(s)` conversion for managed slot keys handles JSON-serialized string keys from stored config entries.\n- The `setdefault(CONF_SLOTS, {})` in adopt correctly avoids clobbering pre-existing slot data, and integer keys match the convention used by `async_step_code_slot`.\n\n**Edge cases:**\n- Exception handling with broad `except Exception` and `# noqa: BLE001` is used consistently for lock communication failures, matching the existing pattern.\n- Missing lock instances (registry lookup failure, unsupported platform, missing config entry) are all gracefully handled with `continue`.\n- PIN conflict across locks during adopt keeps first-seen value and logs a warning.\n- Mixed readable/masked codes during adopt correctly adopts readable ones and clears only masked ones.\n- The `lock_reset` step caches `_unmanaged_codes` on first call to avoid re-querying on menu re-entry.\n- Menu options correctly exclude \"adopt\" when all codes are `SlotCode.UNKNOWN`.\n\n**Strings/translations:**\n- `strings.json` and `translations/en.json` are kept in sync with identical additions.\n- `lock_reset_cancelled` abort reason and `lock_reset` step strings are properly defined.\n\n**Tests:**\n- 12 new test cases cover: skip when no unmanaged codes, clear, adopt, cancel/abort, masked-only codes, mixed codes, missing lock instances, exceptions during clear, PIN conflicts, and direct unit tests of `_async_get_unmanaged_codes`.\n- Tests properly mock `_async_get_unmanaged_codes` at the function level for flow tests and test it directly for unit tests.\n\n**One design note (below confidence threshold, ~60):** When adopting slots and then proceeding to the YAML path, `self.data[CONF_SLOTS] = slots` at line 468 replaces any adopted slots entirely. The user must re-include adopted slots in their YAML submission. The test covers this correctly by passing the adopted slots in the YAML step. This appears intentional but could be surprising to users -- worth considering whether the YAML step should merge rather than replace. This is a product design choice, not a bug.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>41302</total_tokens><tool_uses>22</tool_uses><duration_ms>128520</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/ac8528320e1f3a037.output"},"uuid":"ece8591b-001b-4d23-98fb-3ba4518079eb","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:22:03.240Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
