91-    calls: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n292-\n293-    async def _capture_call(call):\n294-        calls.append({\"service\": call.service, \"data\": dict(call.data)})\n295-        return {LOCK_ENTITY_ID: {}}","numLines":21},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f71d4c29-0721-4d35-a243-3eea3d35d23b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/provider-return-all-slots","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"e2a2bd1b-84cb-4bfb-a6a9-a185188f4163","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DTTN4E9prEKStbG78cCg8G","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This test expects empty dict when no slots configured. Now we also query the lock for all occupied slots, so we need to register the mock service. But the simpler fix: the test is correct that with no configured slots AND no `get_lock_users` service registered, it should return empty. But now we removed the early return. We need to still query the lock — the test needs updating.\n\nActually, the test calls `async_get_usercodes` with no mock service for `get_lock_users`, which will raise. The old code had `if not code_slots: return {}` which skipped the service call entirely. Now we always call the service. The test needs to either register a mock service or we need to handle the \"no managed slots and no occupied slots\" case.\n\nThe right fix: always query the lock (we need to find unmanaged slots), and if the service isn't available, that's a `LockDisconnected` which propagates. The test should register a mock returning empty users:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":449,"cache_read_input_tokens":360065,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":449},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjYS5RRcdEU3JQPxPagj","type":"assistant","uuid":"fdbe2231-ccd1-4010-8c0f-4cf143a98036","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:45:58.228Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/provider-return-all-slots","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
