{"type":"queue-operation","operation":"enqueue","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:55:22.783Z","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","content":"<task-notification>\n<task-id>ad6799593a9ee3fa2</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01M2s7UuqUjzWhecuaZzbRZe</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/ad6799593a9ee3fa2.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Code review PR 988\" completed</summary>\n<result>Now I have a clear picture. Here is my review.\n\n---\n\n## Review: PR #988 (`fix/provider-return-all-slots`)\n\n**Files reviewed:**\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/matter.py`\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/virtual.py`\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/tests/providers/test_matter.py`\n\n### Summary\n\nThe changes make Matter and Virtual providers return all occupied slots (not just managed ones) from `async_get_usercodes()`, aligning with Z-Wave JS behavior. This allows callers like the lock reset config flow to detect unmanaged codes.\n\n### Important (80-89)\n\n**1. Missing test coverage for Virtual provider's new behavior (Confidence: 85)**\n\nFile: `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/tests/providers/test_virtual.py`\n\nThe Virtual provider now returns unmanaged occupied slots (stored slots not in any LCM config entry), but the test file was not updated. The Matter provider got a new `test_get_usercodes_unmanaged_occupied_slots` test, but there is no equivalent for Virtual. Per AGENTS.md: \"Tests go with code changes in same PR.\"\n\n**Fix:** Add a test that populates `_data` with a slot not in any LCM config entry and verifies it appears in the result. For example, set `virtual_lock._data[\"99\"] = {\"code\": \"9999\"}` (where slot 99 is not managed) and assert `codes[99] == \"9999\"`.\n\n**2. Removed early-return optimization causes unnecessary service call (Confidence: 82)**\n\nFile: `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/matter.py` (line 370)\n\nThe old code had `if not code_slots: return {}` which avoided calling `get_lock_users` when no LCM config entry manages this lock. That early return was removed. Now, even when there are zero managed slots, the provider always calls the Matter `get_lock_users` service. This is intentionally needed to discover unmanaged occupied slots, so the behavior change is correct. However, this is a real network call to the Matter controller. If `async_get_usercodes` is called in contexts where only managed slot data is needed (e.g., regular coordinator polling), this adds unnecessary latency for locks with no managed slots.\n\nThis is more of a design consideration than a bug -- if the only caller that needs unmanaged slots is the lock reset flow, consider whether the coordinator polling path should still short-circuit. If this was an intentional decision to keep it simple, no action needed, but worth confirming.\n\n### No Critical Issues Found\n\nThe code logic is correct:\n- The union of `managed_slots | occupied_slots` properly ensures both managed empty slots and unmanaged occupied slots appear in the result.\n- The added `try/except (TypeError, ValueError)` around `int(cred_index)` in Matter is good defensive coding (the `None` check above already handles that case for `TypeError`, but the belt-and-suspenders approach handles unexpected string values).\n- The Virtual provider correctly iterates `_data` keys with `int()` conversion and error handling.\n- The new Matter test properly verifies unmanaged occupied slots appear as `SlotCode.UNKNOWN`.\n- The existing `test_get_usercodes_no_configured_slots` was correctly updated to register a mock service (since the early return was removed, the service is now always called).</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>28120</total_tokens><tool_uses>15</tool_uses><duration_ms>76083</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/ad6799593a9ee3fa2.output"}
