{"parentUuid":"23c67f6e-82e6-41e1-9d76-25972c802632","isSidechain":false,"type":"system","subtype":"turn_duration","durationMs":79560,"timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:56:47.092Z","uuid":"e3aa7386-7f7a-4ee1-9296-d5e739bb8fba","isMeta":false,"userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/provider-return-all-slots","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"e3aa7386-7f7a-4ee1-9296-d5e739bb8fba","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"760def6e-630d-44b8-8abc-6df7947c5e53","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"<task-notification>\n<task-id>a213dab61193ad2aa</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01Fo97KriMoKBXFVPuSTDFEf</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/a213dab61193ad2aa.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Silent failure hunt PR 988\" completed</summary>\n<result>Now I have a thorough understanding of the changes and their downstream effects. Let me compile my audit.\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling Audit: PR #988 (`fix/provider-return-all-slots`)\n\n### Summary\n\nThis PR removes managed-slot filtering from `async_get_usercodes` in the Matter and Virtual providers so that all occupied slots (including unmanaged ones) are returned. The changes are mostly well-structured, but I found several issues ranging from a silent failure to downstream interaction concerns.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 1: Silent Failure -- VirtualLock Swallows Invalid Stored Keys\n\n**Location:** `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/virtual.py`, lines 113-117\n\n**Severity:** MEDIUM\n\n**Issue Description:**\nThe new `stored_slots` loop silently skips keys that fail `int()` conversion with a bare `continue` and no logging:\n\n```python\nfor k in self._data:\n    try:\n        stored_slots.add(int(k))\n    except (TypeError, ValueError):\n        continue\n```\n\nIf `self._data` contains corrupted keys (from storage corruption, migration bugs, or unexpected writes), this silently drops them. The user will never know that some stored data is being ignored. This is a meaningful difference from the Matter provider's equivalent code, which logs a warning for invalid credential indices.\n\n**Hidden Errors:** Storage corruption, migration bugs producing non-integer keys, concurrent writes from other integrations.\n\n**User Impact:** If stored data gets corrupted, the user's codes silently disappear from the returned dict. No log entry exists to help diagnose why a code that was previously set is now gone.\n\n**Recommendation:** Log a warning when skipping invalid keys, matching the pattern used in the Matter provider:\n\n```python\nfor k in self._data:\n    try:\n        stored_slots.add(int(k))\n    except (TypeError, ValueError):\n        _LOGGER.warning(\n            \"Virtual lock %s: skipping stored slot with invalid key %r\",\n            self.lock.entity_id,\n            k,\n        )\n        continue\n```\n\n---\n\n### Issue 2: Managed Slots `int()` Cast Has No Defensive Handling (Pre-existing, Now Higher Impact)\n\n**Location:** `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/matter.py`, line 364; `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/virtual.py`, line 107\n\n**Severity:** MEDIUM\n\n**Issue Description:**\nBoth providers cast `code_slot` from config entry data with `int(code_slot)` inside a set comprehension, with no try/except:\n\n```python\nmanaged_slots = {\n    int(code_slot)\n    for entry in self.hass.config_entries.async_entries(DOMAIN)\n    for code_slot in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_SLOTS, {})\n    if self.lock.entity_id in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_LOCKS, [])\n}\n```\n\nIf `CONF_SLOTS` ever contains a non-integer-convertible key (from data corruption, a bad migration, or an API change), this will raise an unhandled `ValueError` or `TypeError` that propagates up through the coordinator as an `UpdateFailed`, making the entire lock unavailable rather than just skipping one bad slot.\n\nThis is pre-existing code, but the PR increases its impact: previously, the Matter provider had an early `if not code_slots: return {}` guard that would avoid the service call entirely when no managed slots existed. Now, the service call always runs, and any failure in managed_slots construction prevents returning even unmanaged occupied slots -- defeating the purpose of this PR.\n\n**Hidden Errors:** Config entry corruption, migration bugs, YAML import edge cases.\n\n**User Impact:** One corrupted slot key takes down the entire lock's code management instead of gracefully degrading.\n\n**Recommendation:** This is pre-existing and potentially a broader issue across all providers. I am flagging it because the PR's removal of the early-return guard increases the blast radius. Consider wrapping `int(code_slot)` in a try/except with a warning log, or validating at config entry load time.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 3: Duplicate Code Detection Now Includes Unmanaged Slots\n\n**Location:** `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/_base.py`, lines 301-322\n\n**Severity:** HIGH (behavioral change, not strictly an error handling issue but a silent failure path)\n\n**Issue Description:**\n`_check_duplicate_code` iterates over `self.coordinator.data` to find duplicate PINs. With this PR, coordinator data now includes unmanaged occupied slots (as `SlotCode.UNKNOWN`). The check at line 311 calls `self.is_masked_or_empty(other_usercode)` which returns `True` for `SlotCode.UNKNOWN`, so unmanaged UNKNOWN slots are correctly skipped.\n\nHowever, for the Virtual provider, unmanaged slots return their actual PIN code (not `SlotCode.UNKNOWN`). If an unmanaged slot has the same PIN as a managed slot being set, `_check_duplicate_code` will now raise `DuplicateCodeError` and the sync manager will disable the managed slot. The user will see a repair issue saying their code is a duplicate of slot N -- a slot they may not even know about because it is not managed by Lock Code Manager. The error message at `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/_base.py` line 317-322 includes `conflicting_slot_managed=self.is_slot_managed(other_code_slot)`, so the information is available, but the downstream handling and user-facing message should differentiate between \"duplicate of a slot you manage\" and \"duplicate of an unmanaged slot on the lock.\"\n\n**User Impact:** Users could have their managed slots disabled with a confusing error about a conflict with an unmanaged slot they did not configure. This is a behavioral change that may surprise users.\n\n**Recommendation:** This is not strictly an error handling defect but a consequence of the broader data set. Verify that the `DuplicateCodeError` user-facing message (the repair issue text) clearly explains when the conflicting slot is unmanaged. If it does not, update the message to say something like \"conflicts with unmanaged slot N on the lock -- this code may have been set outside of Lock Code Manager.\"\n\n---\n\n### Issue 4: `push_update` Deduplication Is Adequate But Worth Verifying\n\n**Location:** `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/coordinator.py`, lines 100-115\n\n**Severity:** LOW (no defect found)\n\n**Issue Description:**\nThe `push_update` method merges updates into `self.data` via `{**self.data, **updates}` and skips if data has not changed. With unmanaged slots now in `self.data`, the dict grows, but deduplication still works correctly: `new_data == self.data` will be True when nothing changes, preventing redundant listener notifications. The only concern is that the initial poll will now populate coordinator data with unmanaged slots, and subsequent push updates for unmanaged slots will also be stored. This is intentional per the PR description.\n\nNo action needed. The deduplication logic handles the expanded data set correctly.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 5: `_resolve_slot_state` Correctly Guards Against Unmanaged Slots\n\n**Location:** `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/sync.py`, line 223\n\n**Severity:** LOW (no defect found)\n\n**Issue Description:**\nThe sync manager's `_resolve_slot_state` checks `if self._slot_num not in self._coordinator.data` and returns `None`, which causes the tick to retry. Since sync managers are only created for managed slots (by the config entry setup), they will only look up their own `_slot_num` in coordinator data. Unmanaged slots in coordinator data are simply ignored -- they have no sync manager and no entities. This is correct behavior.\n\nNo action needed.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 6: Matter Provider -- Removed Early Return Changes Behavior on Empty Managed Slots\n\n**Location:** `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/matter.py`, lines 362-368 (old lines 367-369 removed)\n\n**Severity:** MEDIUM\n\n**Issue Description:**\nThe old code had:\n```python\nif not code_slots:\n    return {}\n```\n\nThis guard prevented a `get_lock_users` service call when no managed slots existed. The PR removes this guard so that the service call always runs (to discover unmanaged occupied slots). This is intentional, but it means:\n\n1. If the Matter integration is temporarily unavailable, the `_async_call_service` call will raise `LockDisconnected` even when the previous code would have returned `{}` silently. This propagates up to the coordinator as `UpdateFailed`, marking the lock as failed even though there were no managed slots to update.\n\n2. The test `test_get_usercodes_no_configured_slots` was updated to mock the service, confirming this behavioral change is intentional.\n\nThis is not a silent failure -- it is actually the *opposite*: the code now fails louder when it previously would have silently returned empty. This is arguably better behavior (you want to know if the lock is unreachable), but it is a behavioral change worth noting.\n\n**User Impact:** Users with no managed slots configured for a lock will now see coordinator failures when the Matter integration is unavailable, whereas before they would not.\n\n**Recommendation:** This seems intentional and is documented in the test change. No code change needed, but the PR description should call out this behavioral change explicitly.\n\n---\n\n### Pre-existing Issue Worth Noting: Coordinator `async_get_usercodes` Silent Empty Return\n\n**Location:** `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/coordinator.py`, lines 181-191\n\n**Severity:** Already present, not introduced by this PR\n\nThe coordinator's `async_get_usercodes` returns `{}` on first failure (`if not self.last_update_success: return {}`). The comment says \"We can silently fail if we've never been able to retrieve data.\" With the expanded data set from this PR, this means unmanaged slots that were previously loaded could be lost if a subsequent poll fails and `last_update_success` was never True. However, this is pre-existing behavior and not changed by this PR.\n\n---\n\n### Positive Observations\n\n1. **Matter provider's new `int(cred_index)` defensive cast (lines 390-398)** is well done -- it catches `TypeError` and `ValueError`, logs a warning with the lock entity ID and the invalid value, and continues. This is exactly how defensive casts should work.\n\n2. **The debug logging expansion** (lines 401-407) is helpful -- showing managed, occupied, and total counts gives good visibility into the new behavior.\n\n3. **Test coverage** for the new unmanaged-slots-returned behavior is present (`test_get_usercodes_unmanaged_occupied_slots`).\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Actionable Findings\n\n| # | Severity | File | Issue |\n|---|----------|------|-------|\n| 1 | MEDIUM | `virtual.py:113-117` | Silent skip of invalid stored slot keys -- needs warning log |\n| 2 | MEDIUM | Both providers, `managed_slots` comprehension | Unguarded `int()` cast in set comprehension (pre-existing, higher impact now) |\n| 3 | HIGH | `_base.py:301-322` | Duplicate code detection now fires against unmanaged Virtual slots with real PINs -- user-facing message may confuse |\n\nIssue 1 is the only one I would call a **must-fix** before merge. Issue 3 warrants investigation into the downstream user-facing message to ensure it is clear about unmanaged slot conflicts.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>56069</total_tokens><tool_uses>14</tool_uses><duration_ms>109120</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/a213dab61193ad2aa.output"},"uuid":"df66dca6-4b36-49b3-b02f-0e412588d45b","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:56:47.143Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/provider-return-all-slots","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"df66dca6-4b36-49b3-b02f-0e412588d45b","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MS4TYndMdREU2G7G5Cus4R","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two actionable findings:\n\n1. **Virtual silent skip** — add warning log (quick fix)\n2. **Duplicate code detection fires on unmanaged Virtual slots** — this is a real behavioral concern\n\nLet me fix #1 and check #3."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3154,"cache_read_input_tokens":372416,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3154},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjZGwFfD11zq14rAG3GS","type":"assistant","uuid":"6497c22e-b7a3-4be8-8e5f-0ede5c325a41","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:56:57.983Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/provider-return-all-slots","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
