{"parentUuid":"11d4dfb3-5a14-474f-8464-1a21b51c8e6a","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"760def6e-630d-44b8-8abc-6df7947c5e53","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T7PWseTo1QZfT23MBb7RTD","type":"tool_result","content":"301:    def _check_duplicate_code(self, code_slot: int, usercode: str) -> None:\n302-        \"\"\"Raise DuplicateCodeError if the PIN duplicates another slot on this lock.\"\"\"\n303-        # Return early if there's nothing to check\n304-        if not usercode or not self.coordinator or not self.coordinator.data:\n305-            return\n306-        try:\n307-            other_code_slot = next(\n308-                other_code_slot\n309-                for other_code_slot, other_usercode in self.coordinator.data.items()\n310-                if other_code_slot != code_slot\n311-                and not self.is_masked_or_empty(other_usercode)\n312-                and str(other_usercode) == usercode\n313-            )\n314-        except StopIteration:\n315-            pass\n316-        else:\n317-            raise DuplicateCodeError(\n318-                code_slot=code_slot,\n319-                conflicting_slot=other_code_slot,\n320-                conflicting_slot_managed=self.is_slot_managed(other_code_slot),\n321-                lock_entity_id=self.lock.entity_id,\n322-            )\n323-\n324-    @property\n325-    def domain(self) -> str:\n326-        \"\"\"Return integration domain.\"\"\"\n327-        raise NotImplementedError()\n328-\n329-    @property\n330-    def usercode_scan_interval(self) -> timedelta:\n331-        \"\"\"Return scan interval for usercodes.\"\"\""}]},"uuid":"2d674b05-03b3-48ed-9ceb-34c81411e278","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:57:10.408Z","toolUseResult":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"301:    def _check_duplicate_code(self, code_slot: int, usercode: str) -> None:\n302-        \"\"\"Raise DuplicateCodeError if the PIN duplicates another slot on this lock.\"\"\"\n303-        # Return early if there's nothing to check\n304-        if not usercode or not self.coordinator or not self.coordinator.data:\n305-            return\n306-        try:\n307-            other_code_slot = next(\n308-                other_code_slot\n309-                for other_code_slot, other_usercode in self.coordinator.data.items()\n310-                if other_code_slot != code_slot\n311-                and not self.is_masked_or_empty(other_usercode)\n312-                and str(other_usercode) == usercode\n313-            )\n314-        except StopIteration:\n315-            pass\n316-        else:\n317-            raise DuplicateCodeError(\n318-                code_slot=code_slot,\n319-                conflicting_slot=other_code_slot,\n320-                conflicting_slot_managed=self.is_slot_managed(other_code_slot),\n321-                lock_entity_id=self.lock.entity_id,\n322-            )\n323-\n324-    @property\n325-    def domain(self) -> str:\n326-        \"\"\"Return integration domain.\"\"\"\n327-        raise NotImplementedError()\n328-\n329-    @property\n330-    def usercode_scan_interval(self) -> timedelta:\n331-        \"\"\"Return scan interval for usercodes.\"\"\"","numLines":31},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"11d4dfb3-5a14-474f-8464-1a21b51c8e6a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/provider-return-all-slots","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"2d674b05-03b3-48ed-9ceb-34c81411e278","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TogoYkpnPkDkwAKs7xMTWa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Looking at the duplicate check: line 311 calls `self.is_masked_or_empty(other_usercode)` which returns `True` for `SlotCode.UNKNOWN` and `SlotCode.EMPTY`. For Matter, unmanaged slots are `UNKNOWN` — skipped correctly. For Virtual, unmanaged slots have real PIN values — they WOULD trigger duplicate detection.\n\nThis is actually correct behavior for Z-Wave (which already returns all slots). If an unmanaged slot on a Z-Wave lock has the same PIN as a managed slot, duplicate detection fires. The Virtual provider is now consistent with that. The `conflicting_slot_managed=self.is_slot_managed(other_code_slot)` flag tells the downstream handler it's an unmanaged slot.\n\nLet me check how the error message uses this flag:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1497,"cache_read_input_tokens":376101,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1497},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjZJNoLViV2Q62tPfZKy","type":"assistant","uuid":"3bca9afe-ae9a-41ca-a4f0-7ef2b6cf7308","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:57:19.128Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/provider-return-all-slots","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
