{"parentUuid":"5e3e699e-17b1-455e-8247-9102fc270b83","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"97ed883d-d33c-45cd-9f31-4358d93ee749","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"right but also, if I was managing slot 1, and I update to include slot 2, if it's a matter lock, slot 1 will show as unknown. We can reset it if we want to be safe but we should note that's what's happening"},"uuid":"cfb27292-b74d-44ca-bf15-73a264a2c113","timestamp":"2026-04-04T23:11:15.917Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"cfb27292-b74d-44ca-bf15-73a264a2c113","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KnzA2B6N68519xADgNJH2b","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood point. In the options flow with Matter:\n\n1. User manages slot 1 (PIN set, shows UNKNOWN)\n2. User adds slot 2 in options\n3. Lock reset runs on the updated lock → queries `async_get_usercodes`\n4. Slot 1 returns as UNKNOWN — it's managed by this entry, but `managed_slots` is computed from the *current* config which still has slot 1, so it's filtered out ✓\n5. Slot 2 (if occupied) shows as unmanaged → offered for adopt/clear ✓\n\nActually that works. But the tricky case: what if the user *removes* slot 1 from the config in the same update? Then slot 1 is no longer managed → shows as \"unmanaged UNKNOWN\" → offered for clear. That's actually correct behavior — you're no longer managing it, so offering to clear it makes sense.\n\nThe real issue you're raising: if we re-set all managed slots \"to be safe\" after lock reset, we'd re-set slot 1's PIN even though nothing changed. For Matter that's harmless (write-only, same PIN), but it's unnecessary churn and the user should know it's happening.\n\nThis is all options-flow behavior though. Let me make sure the TODO captures these nuances:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":274,"cache_read_input_tokens":394163,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":274},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjaNyRAis7NVZUwSoLRD","type":"assistant","uuid":"49cd7f55-ab44-49c7-b2bb-a2e252b677c9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T23:11:31.572Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
