{"parentUuid":"05f4097a-fa58-4c30-928b-14fd2c33d672","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018potjUQdJMjdPqNfGina6S","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There it is. The same `managed_slots` comprehension is copy-pasted in **5 places**: Matter, Virtual, Z-Wave, Akuvox, Schlage, and the config flow. Akuvox and Schlage already extracted it to `_get_managed_slots()` on the provider class.\n\nTwo clear reusable pieces:\n\n1. **`get_managed_slots(hass, lock_entity_id)`** — a module-level function in `data.py` (next to `find_entry_for_lock_slot` which does the same scan). Every provider and the config flow could use it.\n\n2. **\"For each lock's codes, clear slot with error handling\"** — used in both `async_step_lock_reset_clear` and the masked-slot clearing in `async_step_lock_reset_adopt`. Same try/except/warning pattern.\n\n\\#1 is the bigger win — eliminates duplication across 6 files. Want me to extract `get_managed_slots` to `data.py` and update all consumers? That would be a separate PR since it touches all providers."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1727,"cache_read_input_tokens":420494,"output_tokens":259,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1727,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjfH5f8AbqhLppkCVMnF","type":"assistant","uuid":"ba3566a9-084f-468e-b5e5-7c97d828b23f","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:15:44.422Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
