{"parentUuid":"8704c737-33e8-45bd-9875-68f92dc1f85e","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"463050f8-11e5-47bc-ba96-5b447a4cfca8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JdrM5QzS34hdq4z8Z57dVM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Async agent launched successfully.\nagentId: a5fde46edf06f12a2 (internal ID - do not mention to user. Use SendMessage with to: 'a5fde46edf06f12a2' to continue this agent.)\nThe agent is working in the background. You will be notified automatically when it completes.\nDo not duplicate this agent's work — avoid working with the same files or topics it is using. Work on non-overlapping tasks, or briefly tell the user what you launched and end your response.\noutput_file: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/a5fde46edf06f12a2.output\nIf asked, you can check progress before completion by using Read or Bash tail on the output file."}]}]},"uuid":"222345c6-0e76-4428-be57-daeb3b221be5","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:17:11.608Z","toolUseResult":{"isAsync":true,"status":"async_launched","agentId":"a5fde46edf06f12a2","description":"Extract get_managed_slots and _clear_slots","prompt":"Create a PR that extracts two reusable pieces from the lock_code_manager codebase at /Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager.\n\nCreate branch `refactor/extract-managed-slots-helper` from `main`.\n\n## Change 1: Extract `get_managed_slots` to `data.py`\n\nThe same \"managed slots\" comprehension is copy-pasted across 6 files. Extract it to a single function in `data.py`:\n\n```python\ndef get_managed_slots(hass: HomeAssistant, lock_entity_id: str) -> set[int]:\n    \"\"\"Return the set of slot numbers managed by any LCM config entry for a lock.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        int(code_slot)\n        for entry in hass.config_entries.async_entries(DOMAIN)\n        for code_slot in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_SLOTS, {})\n        if lock_entity_id in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_LOCKS, [])\n    }\n```\n\nThen update ALL consumers to use it. Search for this pattern across the codebase:\n```python\n{\n    int(code_slot)\n    for entry in self.hass.config_entries.async_entries(DOMAIN)\n    for code_slot in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_SLOTS, {})\n    if self.lock.entity_id in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_LOCKS, [])\n}\n```\n\nFiles to update (verify by searching):\n- `custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/matter.py` — replace inline comprehension with `get_managed_slots(self.hass, self.lock.entity_id)`\n- `custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/virtual.py` — same\n- `custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/zwave_js.py` — same (variable is `code_slots` there)\n- `custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/akuvox.py` — has `_get_managed_slots()` method, replace body with call to `get_managed_slots`\n- `custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/schlage.py` — same as akuvox\n- `custom_components/lock_code_manager/config_flow.py` — replace inline comprehension in `_async_get_unmanaged_codes`\n\nFor akuvox and schlage, keep the `_get_managed_slots` method but make it delegate:\n```python\ndef _get_managed_slots(self) -> set[int]:\n    \"\"\"Return managed slot numbers for this lock.\"\"\"\n    return get_managed_slots(self.hass, self.lock.entity_id)\n```\n\nImport `get_managed_slots` from `..data` in each provider, and from `.data` in config_flow.py.\n\n## Change 2: Extract `_clear_slots` helper in config_flow.py\n\nIn `config_flow.py`, the \"clear slots with error handling\" pattern appears twice (in `async_step_lock_reset_clear` and the masked-slot clearing in `async_step_lock_reset_adopt`). Extract a method on the flow class:\n\n```python\nasync def _clear_slots(self, slots_to_clear: dict[str, list[int]]) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Clear specified slots on each lock, logging failures.\"\"\"\n    for lock_entity_id, slots in slots_to_clear.items():\n        lock_instance = self._lock_instances.get(lock_entity_id)\n        if not lock_instance:\n            _LOGGER.warning(\n                \"No lock instance for %s; cannot clear codes\",\n                lock_entity_id,\n            )\n            continue\n        for slot in slots:\n            try:\n                await lock_instance.async_internal_clear_usercode(\n                    slot, source=\"direct\"\n                )\n            except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001\n                _LOGGER.warning(\n                    \"Failed to clear slot %s on %s\",\n                    slot, lock_entity_id, exc_info=True,\n                )\n```\n\nThen update:\n- `async_step_lock_reset_clear`: replace the loop with `await self._clear_slots({lock_id: list(codes) for lock_id, codes in self._unmanaged_codes.items()})`\n- `async_step_lock_reset_adopt` masked clearing: replace with `await self._clear_slots({lock_id: [s for s, c in codes.items() if c is SlotCode.UNKNOWN] for lock_id, codes in self._unmanaged_codes.items()})`\n\nIMPORTANT: The config_flow.py on the `main` branch does NOT have the lock reset step yet (that's PR #983). So for the config_flow.py changes, only extract `get_managed_slots` — do NOT add the `_clear_slots` method or lock reset code. The `_clear_slots` extraction will happen when PR #983 is rebased onto this.\n\nActually wait — let me reconsider. Since this PR is from main and config_flow.py on main doesn't have the lock reset code, the `_clear_slots` extraction and `get_managed_slots` usage in config_flow can't be done here. Only do config_flow changes that apply to what's on main. If config_flow.py on main doesn't use managed_slots at all, skip it entirely.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. Create branch from main\n2. Add `get_managed_slots` to `data.py`\n3. Update all provider files to use it\n4. Update tests if any directly test the old pattern\n5. Run `uv run pytest -x -q` — all tests must pass\n6. Run `uv run pre-commit run --all-files` — must be clean\n7. Commit and push\n8. Create PR with description using the project's template (NO breaking change section since there isn't one)\n\nConvention reminders:\n- Never use inline imports\n- Import from canonical modules (e.g., `from ..data import get_managed_slots`)\n- Tests go with code changes","outputFile":"/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/a5fde46edf06f12a2.output","canReadOutputFile":true},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8704c737-33e8-45bd-9875-68f92dc1f85e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"worktree-agent-a5fde46e","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
