{"type":"queue-operation","operation":"enqueue","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:24:37.061Z","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","content":"<task-notification>\n<task-id>a5fde46edf06f12a2</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01JdrM5QzS34hdq4z8Z57dVM</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-raman-projects-lock-code-manager/453e0149-376f-4dc6-bc77-552585a773b9/tasks/a5fde46edf06f12a2.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Extract get_managed_slots and _clear_slots\" completed</summary>\n<result>PR created: https://github.com/raman325/lock_code_manager/pull/989\n\nSummary of what was done:\n\n**Change 1: Extracted `get_managed_slots` to `data.py`**\n\nAdded `get_managed_slots(hass, lock_entity_id) -> set[int]` to `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/.claude/worktrees/agent-a5fde46e/custom_components/lock_code_manager/data.py`, replacing the identical 5-line set comprehension that was duplicated across 5 provider files.\n\nUpdated consumers:\n- `providers/matter.py` -- replaced inline comprehension with `get_managed_slots(self.hass, self.lock.entity_id)`\n- `providers/virtual.py` -- same\n- `providers/zwave_js.py` -- same (variable name `code_slots` preserved)\n- `providers/akuvox.py` -- `_get_managed_slots()` method kept as thin delegate\n- `providers/schlage.py` -- same as akuvox\n\nUnused imports (`CONF_LOCKS`, `CONF_SLOTS`, `DOMAIN`, `get_entry_data`) were cleaned up from each provider file.\n\n**Change 2: `_clear_slots` extraction skipped** -- as noted in the task, `config_flow.py` on `main` does not have the lock reset step code, so this extraction will happen when PR #983 is rebased.\n\nAll 536 tests pass, all pre-commit checks are clean.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>64819</total_tokens><tool_uses>125</tool_uses><duration_ms>445501</duration_ms></usage>\n<worktree><worktreePath>/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/.claude/worktrees/agent-a5fde46e</worktreePath><worktreeBranch>worktree-agent-a5fde46e</worktr