{"parentUuid":"026bc3ab-f549-4c0c-bd35-364072750a8d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01W9dW5aFu1iUTduZkwNcRUR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014rhy86GmGTK6gamzkT9bP4","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gh issue view 984 --json comments --jq '.comments[] | {author: .author.login, createdAt: .createdAt, body: .body[:600]}' 2>&1","description":"Check all 984 comments"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":104,"cache_read_input_tokens":445140,"output_tokens":119,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":104,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjyyiQvgtfbJvPYrNEZ1","type":"assistant","uuid":"c8905232-f417-4cfa-9f7e-72e21152c8f0","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:20:54.551Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"c8905232-f417-4cfa-9f7e-72e21152c8f0","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"3e7ca2d0-4520-4bc1-9822-ba0cf0079be9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014rhy86GmGTK6gamzkT9bP4","type":"tool_result","content":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"for 2 + 3 I hadn't implemented event support on Matter locks yet because Claude told me that it wasn't support. Quick Google says Claude was wrong so linked PR will address it\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T01:52:09Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"for 1, when you disable the slot, what happens? the name and PIN fields you see there won't change, but the active sensor at the bottom should go to off\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T01:52:57Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"jprasm\",\"body\":\"for 1, when I disable the slot, the active sensor goes off. \\n\\n\\u003cimg width=\\\"340\\\" height=\\\"709\\\" alt=\\\"Image\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/076d5eef-60ad-4800-8bc7-97e75e279fc3\\\" /\\u003e\\n\\nI've installed the latest update. Events still greyed out (as you can see). Went to the lock and all codes still work, even the ones I've disabled. \\n\\nI'm also listening to lock_code_manager_lock_state_changed events, and I haven't seen any events at all. \\n\\nLet me know what I can provide you for help!\\n\\n\\nA couple of other screenshots (I don't know what the amber color icon i lock status means)\\n\\u003cimg width=\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T11:12:21Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"Thanks for the details! Let's work through each:\\n\\n**For the disabled codes still working:** When you disable a slot, the sync manager should clear the PIN on the lock. Can you enable debug logging for Lock Code Manager and share the logs? Add this to your `configuration.yaml`:\\n\\n```yaml\\nlogger:\\n  logs:\\n    custom_components.lock_code_manager: debug\\n```\\n\\nThen restart HA, disable a slot, wait ~10 seconds, and share the relevant logs. I'm looking for:\\n- `Clearing usercode on lock.xxx slot N` — confirms the clear was attempted\\n- Any `Matter service matter.clear_lock_credential failed` errors\\n- Any \",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T12:55:56Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"lets also add homeassistant.components.matter to debug:\\n\\n```yaml\\nlogger:\\n  logs:\\n    custom_components.lock_code_manager: debug\\n    homeassistant.components.matter: debug\\n```\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T12:57:10Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"jprasm\",\"body\":\"I really apprecaite you helping me here!\\n\\n1. Matter integration shows both U200 locks:\\n\\n\\u003cimg width=\\\"1035\\\" height=\\\"525\\\" alt=\\\"Image\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/89cc8a68-f8b3-4d4a-9707-e9ee513ada08\\\" /\\u003e\\n\\n2. I'm using HA version 2026.4.1\\n\\nHere is a sample of the logs (let me know if you need more)....there are indeed some errors here.\\n\\n**I'm seeing a lot of this:**\\n\\n2026-04-04 10:29:05.722 DEBUG (MainThread) [custom_components.lock_code_manager.providers] Lock lock.door_to_garage: push subscription deferred: Matter client or node ID unavailable for lock.door_to_garage\\n2026-04-0\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T14:46:03Z\"}","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"f800b9a6-7ac1-42db-81e0-e74db91bc8b2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:20:56.018Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"for 2 + 3 I hadn't implemented event support on Matter locks yet because Claude told me that it wasn't support. Quick Google says Claude was wrong so linked PR will address it\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T01:52:09Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"for 1, when you disable the slot, what happens? the name and PIN fields you see there won't change, but the active sensor at the bottom should go to off\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T01:52:57Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"jprasm\",\"body\":\"for 1, when I disable the slot, the active sensor goes off. \\n\\n\\u003cimg width=\\\"340\\\" height=\\\"709\\\" alt=\\\"Image\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/076d5eef-60ad-4800-8bc7-97e75e279fc3\\\" /\\u003e\\n\\nI've installed the latest update. Events still greyed out (as you can see). Went to the lock and all codes still work, even the ones I've disabled. \\n\\nI'm also listening to lock_code_manager_lock_state_changed events, and I haven't seen any events at all. \\n\\nLet me know what I can provide you for help!\\n\\n\\nA couple of other screenshots (I don't know what the amber color icon i lock status means)\\n\\u003cimg width=\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T11:12:21Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"Thanks for the details! Let's work through each:\\n\\n**For the disabled codes still working:** When you disable a slot, the sync manager should clear the PIN on the lock. Can you enable debug logging for Lock Code Manager and share the logs? Add this to your `configuration.yaml`:\\n\\n```yaml\\nlogger:\\n  logs:\\n    custom_components.lock_code_manager: debug\\n```\\n\\nThen restart HA, disable a slot, wait ~10 seconds, and share the relevant logs. I'm looking for:\\n- `Clearing usercode on lock.xxx slot N` — confirms the clear was attempted\\n- Any `Matter service matter.clear_lock_credential failed` errors\\n- Any \",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T12:55:56Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"raman325\",\"body\":\"lets also add homeassistant.components.matter to debug:\\n\\n```yaml\\nlogger:\\n  logs:\\n    custom_components.lock_code_manager: debug\\n    homeassistant.components.matter: debug\\n```\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T12:57:10Z\"}\n{\"author\":\"jprasm\",\"body\":\"I really apprecaite you helping me here!\\n\\n1. Matter integration shows both U200 locks:\\n\\n\\u003cimg width=\\\"1035\\\" height=\\\"525\\\" alt=\\\"Image\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/89cc8a68-f8b3-4d4a-9707-e9ee513ada08\\\" /\\u003e\\n\\n2. I'm using HA version 2026.4.1\\n\\nHere is a sample of the logs (let me know if you need more)....there are indeed some errors here.\\n\\n**I'm seeing a lot of this:**\\n\\n2026-04-04 10:29:05.722 DEBUG (MainThread) [custom_components.lock_code_manager.providers] Lock lock.door_to_garage: push subscription deferred: Matter client or node ID unavailable for lock.door_to_garage\\n2026-04-0\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-04T14:46:03Z\"}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c8905232-f417-4cfa-9f7e-72e21152c8f0","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
