{"parentUuid":"32673eb5-d296-4f38-9234-5845844bd81d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HRiNWXQGUCYyks5fjw36Jf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two key findings from the user's logs:\n\n1. **Push subscription failing**: `Matter client or node ID unavailable for lock.door_to_garage` — this means `_get_matter_client()` or `_matter_node_id` is returning None. The push framework retries every 10s but keeps failing. This explains why events are unavailable.\n\n2. **`duplicate` status on set_lock_credential**: The Matter lock is returning \"duplicate\" when trying to set a credential. This means the lock already has a credential at that index and the Matter service is refusing to overwrite it. This is different from Z-Wave — Matter's `set_lock_credential` may require clearing first before re-setting.\n\nThe duplicate issue is the root cause for codes not clearing when disabled. The sync flow is: disable slot → clear usercode → but the log shows it's trying to **set** usercode, not clear. Let me check — the user said \"all codes still work, even the ones I've disabled.\" The sync manager should clear on disable, but the log shows set operations failing with duplicate.\n\nLet me look at the `_matter_node_id` issue — that's likely why events don't work:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":642,"cache_read_input_tokens":446318,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":642},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjyzpUap9Pa2eGkhCn3i","type":"assistant","uuid":"ef203e22-d59f-4984-ad4d-0a0c508b73ee","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:21:14.089Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":