{"parentUuid":"b84d8bfb-e445-4ff3-bb9b-8d6ae6f7c2a8","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"3e7ca2d0-4520-4bc1-9822-ba0cf0079be9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pv54U85cJuHyBNq8Cga5Sb","type":"tool_result","content":"   240→\n   241→    @final\n   242→    @callback\n   243→    def __post_init__(self) -> None:\n   244→        \"\"\"Post initialization.\"\"\"\n   245→        if not (device_id := self.lock.device_id):\n   246→            return\n   247→        self.device_entry = self.dev_reg.async_get(device_id)\n   248→\n   249→    @final\n   250→    def __repr__(self) -> str:\n   251→        \"\"\"Return string representation of self.\"\"\"\n   252→        return f\"{self.__class__.__name__}(domain={self.domain}, lock={self.lock.entity_id})\"\n   253→\n   254→    @final"}]},"uuid":"1acc12de-8d1f-46ea-acff-af4007bea1b6","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:21:32.564Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/_base.py","content":"\n    @final\n    @callback\n    def __post_init__(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Post initialization.\"\"\"\n        if not (device_id := self.lock.device_id):\n            return\n        self.device_entry = self.dev_reg.async_get(device_id)\n\n    @final\n    def __repr__(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Return string representation of self.\"\"\"\n        return f\"{self.__class__.__name__}(domain={self.domain}, lock={self.lock.entity_id})\"\n\n    @final","numLines":15,"startLine":240,"totalLines":1001}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b84d8bfb-e445-4ff3-bb9b-8d6ae6f7c2a8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"1acc12de-8d1f-46ea-acff-af4007bea1b6","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017skxPFnQ6Qp45P4eNJS8nT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So `device_entry` is set in `__post_init__` from `self.lock.device_id`. If the lock entity has no `device_id`, `device_entry` stays None and `_matter_node_id` returns None.\n\nThe user's lock entities should have device IDs since they show up in the Matter integration's device page. But maybe `self.lock` (which is an entity registry entry) doesn't have `device_id` populated yet at the time `__post_init__` runs.\n\nActually, looking at the log more carefully: `\"Matter client or node ID unavailable\"` — this is the error from `setup_push_subscription`. It could be either the client or the node ID. The retry keeps firing every 10s, suggesting it never resolves.\n\nLet me draft a response asking for specific diagnostic info:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":302,"cache_read_input_tokens":448299,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":302},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjz318Ljy16uz74LmGSf","type":"assistant","uuid":"2baad3b8-d6e2-47fc-a8fb-3096022d351a","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:21:41.203Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"2baad3b8-d6e2-47fc-a8fb-3096022d351a","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017skxPFnQ6Qp45P4eNJS8nT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BQXgu9THA2t86UfFbPVUoj","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gh issue comment 984 --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nThanks for the logs! Two issues visible:\n\n**1. Push subscription failing (\"Matter client or node ID unavailable\")**\n\nThis is why the event entity is greyed out. The lock provider can't find the Matter client or resolve the node ID from the device registry. Can you check:\n\n1. In Developer Tools → States, search for `lock.door_to_garage` — does it show a `device_id` in the attributes?\n2. In Developer Tools → Template, paste this and share the result:\n```jinja\n{% set lock = states.lock.door_to_garage %}\ndevice_id: {{ lock.attributes.get('device_id', 'NOT SET') }}\nentity_id: {{ lock.entity_id }}\n```\n3. Also check: Settings → Devices → find the Door to Garage lock → what identifiers does it show? The Matter integration should show something like `matter: <node_id>`.\n\n**2. \"duplicate\" status on set_lock_credential**\n\nThe Aqara U200 is rejecting the `set_lock_credential` call with status \"duplicate.\" This means the credential index already has a PIN stored and the Matter service is refusing to overwrite it. This is a Matter spec behavior — some locks require you to **clear** the credential first before setting a new one at the same index.\n\nThis is a bug in our Matter provider — we should clear-then-set instead of just set. I'll open a fix for this.\n\n**3. Codes not clearing when slot disabled**\n\nThe logs show `set usercode` operations failing, but I don't see `Clearing usercode` messages. When you disable a slot:\n- Do you see `Clearing usercode on lock.door_to_garage slot N` in the logs?\n- Or does it just show the set failures?\n\nIf no clear messages appear, the sync manager might not be detecting the state change correctly. The debug logs from disabling a specific slot would help narrow this down.\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Comment on issue 984"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":302,"cache_read_input_tokens":448299,"output_tokens":726,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":302,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjz318Ljy16uz74LmGSf","type":"assistant","uuid":"2285e1da-c845-4c36-b6af-761d82b3f2e2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:21:50.777Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
