{"parentUuid":"9361d31c-003f-4b87-bff7-5dfd225d7266","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"e233c303-8cf0-470d-8a6e-94541fdb4d40","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"is it a duplicate or a n overwriting issue? those aren't necessarily the same thing"},"uuid":"328bce89-2af7-4fa3-a3bf-a0ccc7ccbc14","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:24:26.717Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"328bce89-2af7-4fa3-a3bf-a0ccc7ccbc14","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JYAMAGi5Yq39doXYUF48xd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood point. Looking at the log message again:\n\n> `Failed to set credential: lock returned status `duplicate``\n\nIn the Matter spec, \"duplicate\" specifically means the **credential data** (the PIN value itself) already exists on the lock in a **different** slot. It's the lock saying \"this PIN is already assigned to another user/credential index.\" It's not about overwriting the same slot — it's about PIN uniqueness across all slots.\n\nSo the Aqara U200 might have the same PIN set on a different slot (maybe from before LCM took over), and the lock is refusing to allow the same PIN on two slots. This is actually the same concept as Z-Wave's event 15 (duplicate code rejection).\n\nThis means:\n1. The \"duplicate\" error is not about clearing first — it's about the PIN value already existing elsewhere on the lock\n2. The user probably has codes set on the lock from before LCM was configured\n3. LCM tries to set the same PIN on a managed slot, lock says \"that PIN already exists on slot X\"\n\nThis ties directly into the lock reset step (PR #983) — if the user had run through lock reset, the unmanaged codes would have been cleared first, avoiding the duplicate. It also means we should handle this error specifically in the Matter provider, similar to how Z-Wave handles event 15.\n\nShould I add `duplicate` handling to the Matter provider as a separate PR?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":114,"cache_read_input_tokens":449942,"output_tokens":323,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":114,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjzGAfgst9NNtk9dHL8v","type":"assistant","uuid":"03fde52c-a3ea-40b7-ae45-84c5cb0b5dd2","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:24:44.431Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
