{"parentUuid":"312c5c0b-b1fb-433d-8214-9c0dda953d4b","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"b607bdf8-2113-4e15-811f-92845fdc2d32","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01G6sAuwJzUhPn9wBmY6dvqS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I understand the flow. The `send_command` at line 297-315 is calling `self._chip_controller.SendCommand` which is the PyMATTER SDK's SendCommand. The response will be the SetCredentialResponse which contains the `status` field. Now let me verify the SetCredentialResponse structure again to see what it returns, and check what happens when the status is `kDuplicate` (0x02):\n\nBased on my research, here's my complete analysis:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\nI've found the structured way to detect \"duplicate\" status from the Matter lock's `set_lock_credential` service. Here's what the chain looks like:\n\n### 1. **SetCredentialResponse Structure** (`chip/clusters/Objects.py`)\nThe Matter DoorLock cluster defines the SetCredential command response as:\n\n```python\nclass SetCredentialResponse(ClusterCommand):\n    status: DoorLock.Enums.DlStatus = 0\n    userIndex: typing.Union[Nullable, uint] = NullValue\n    nextCredentialIndex: typing.Union[Nullable, uint] = NullValue\n```\n\n### 2. **DlStatus Enum** (the structured status code)\n```python\nclass DlStatus(MatterIntEnum):\n    kSuccess = 0x00\n    kFailure = 0x01\n    kDuplicate = 0x02          # <-- DUPLICATE STATUS\n    kOccupied = 0x03\n    kInvalidField = 0x85\n    kResourceExhausted = 0x89\n    kNotFound = 0x8B\n```\n\n### 3. **Flow Through the Stack**\n- Home Assistant's Matter lock entity calls the service via `send_device_command`\n- This calls through to `matter_server/server/device_controller.py::send_device_command()` (line 687-724)\n- Which calls `ChipDeviceControllerWrapper.send_command()` (line 297-315 in `sdk.py`)\n- Which calls the underlying PyMATTER SDK's `SendCommand()`\n- The SDK parses the device response into a `SetCredentialResponse` object with a `status` field\n\n### 4. **Current String-Based Detection** (your code at line 431 in matter.py)\nYour current code catches errors with:\n```python\nif \"duplicate\" in str(err).lower():\n```\n\nThis is **fragile** because:\n- The error message is stringified from a `MatterError`\n- The error handling in HA's `catch_matter_error` decorator (entity.py line 55-69) converts MatterError to HomeAssistantError with just the string message\n\n### 5. **Better Structured Approach**\nInstead of string matching, you should:\n\n1. **Access the response object directly** from `send_device_command` if it returns the SetCredentialResponse\n2. **Check the status field** against `DoorLock.Enums.DlStatus.kDuplicate` (value 0x02)\n3. **Handle it at the command level**, not the error string level\n\n**Exact imports you'd need:**\n```python\nfrom chip.clusters import Objects as Clusters\nDlStatus = Clusters.DoorLock.Enums.DlStatus\n# Then check: response.status == DlStatus.kDuplicate (0x02)\n```\n\n### 6. **Key Files for Reference**\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/chip/clusters/Objects.py` - Lines 26796 (DlStatus) and 27589 (SetCredentialResponse)\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/homeassistant/components/matter/entity.py` - Lines 55-69 (error wrapping)\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/matter.py` - Lines 420-436 (current detection)\n\nThe status code `0x02` is a **structured, documented part of the Matter DoorLock cluster specification** — far more reliable than string matching on error messages that can vary by implementation or localization."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8cfb461256633736 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8cfb461256633736' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 117258\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 113400</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"8922b43b-24fb-4733-aa7a-6a8b0ceb6a87","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:29:03.945Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the Home Assistant Matter integration source code to understand how the \"duplicate\" status is returned from `set_lock_credential` service.\n\nLook in the HA core Matter integration (likely at homeassistant/components/matter/) for:\n1. The `set_lock_credential` service handler\n2. How it processes the lock's response status\n3. What exception type it raises for \"duplicate\" status specifically\n4. Whether the exception has any structured data (like a status code) vs just a string message\n\nAlso check the python-matter-server library for how credential set responses are structured.\n\nSearch in:\n- The installed HA core package: find files related to matter lock services\n- The python-matter-server package in .venv\n\nI need to know if there's a more structured way to detect \"duplicate\" than string matching on the error message.","agentId":"a8cfb461256633736","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I understand the flow. The `send_command` at line 297-315 is calling `self._chip_controller.SendCommand` which is the PyMATTER SDK's SendCommand. The response will be the SetCredentialResponse which contains the `status` field. Now let me verify the SetCredentialResponse structure again to see what it returns, and check what happens when the status is `kDuplicate` (0x02):\n\nBased on my research, here's my complete analysis:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\nI've found the structured way to detect \"duplicate\" status from the Matter lock's `set_lock_credential` service. Here's what the chain looks like:\n\n### 1. **SetCredentialResponse Structure** (`chip/clusters/Objects.py`)\nThe Matter DoorLock cluster defines the SetCredential command response as:\n\n```python\nclass SetCredentialResponse(ClusterCommand):\n    status: DoorLock.Enums.DlStatus = 0\n    userIndex: typing.Union[Nullable, uint] = NullValue\n    nextCredentialIndex: typing.Union[Nullable, uint] = NullValue\n```\n\n### 2. **DlStatus Enum** (the structured status code)\n```python\nclass DlStatus(MatterIntEnum):\n    kSuccess = 0x00\n    kFailure = 0x01\n    kDuplicate = 0x02          # <-- DUPLICATE STATUS\n    kOccupied = 0x03\n    kInvalidField = 0x85\n    kResourceExhausted = 0x89\n    kNotFound = 0x8B\n```\n\n### 3. **Flow Through the Stack**\n- Home Assistant's Matter lock entity calls the service via `send_device_command`\n- This calls through to `matter_server/server/device_controller.py::send_device_command()` (line 687-724)\n- Which calls `ChipDeviceControllerWrapper.send_command()` (line 297-315 in `sdk.py`)\n- Which calls the underlying PyMATTER SDK's `SendCommand()`\n- The SDK parses the device response into a `SetCredentialResponse` object with a `status` field\n\n### 4. **Current String-Based Detection** (your code at line 431 in matter.py)\nYour current code catches errors with:\n```python\nif \"duplicate\" in str(err).lower():\n```\n\nThis is **fragile** because:\n- The error message is stringified from a `MatterError`\n- The error handling in HA's `catch_matter_error` decorator (entity.py line 55-69) converts MatterError to HomeAssistantError with just the string message\n\n### 5. **Better Structured Approach**\nInstead of string matching, you should:\n\n1. **Access the response object directly** from `send_device_command` if it returns the SetCredentialResponse\n2. **Check the status field** against `DoorLock.Enums.DlStatus.kDuplicate` (value 0x02)\n3. **Handle it at the command level**, not the error string level\n\n**Exact imports you'd need:**\n```python\nfrom chip.clusters import Objects as Clusters\nDlStatus = Clusters.DoorLock.Enums.DlStatus\n# Then check: response.status == DlStatus.kDuplicate (0x02)\n```\n\n### 6. **Key Files for Reference**\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/chip/clusters/Objects.py` - Lines 26796 (DlStatus) and 27589 (SetCredentialResponse)\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/homeassistant/components/matter/entity.py` - Lines 55-69 (error wrapping)\n- `/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/matter.py` - Lines 420-436 (current detection)\n\nThe status code `0x02` is a **structured, documented part of the Matter DoorLock cluster specification** — far more reliable than string matching on error messages that can vary by implementation or localization."}],"totalDurationMs":113400,"totalTokens":117258,"totalToolUseCount":44,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4433,"cache_read_input_tokens":111810,"output_tokens":1015,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4433},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"312c5c0b-b1fb-433d-8214-9c0dda953d4b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"8922b43b-24fb-4733-aa7a-6a8b0ceb6a87","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019zs4xb9q1ge2cyNKeoN1GK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The structured status code exists (`DlStatus.kDuplicate = 0x02`), but the problem is that by the time it reaches our code, HA's Matter integration has already converted it to a `HomeAssistantError` with just a string message. We don't get the raw `SetCredentialResponse`.\n\nThe chain is:\n1. Lock returns `SetCredentialResponse(status=kDuplicate)`\n2. HA Matter integration checks status, raises `HomeAssistantError(\"Failed to set credential: lock returned status `duplicate`\")`\n3. Our `_async_call_service` catches it, re-raises as `LockDisconnected`\n4. We only have the string\n\nWe can't access the structured response without either:\n- **A)** Calling the Matter server directly (bypassing HA services) to get the raw response\n- **B)** Matching on the error string (fragile but workable since HA controls the message format)\n- **C)** Requesting the HA Matter integration expose the status code in the exception or response data\n\nB is the pragmatic approach for now. The string `\"duplicate\"` comes from the DlStatus enum name which is spec-defined and unlikely to change. But let me check if the service response includes the status:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1413,"cache_read_input_tokens":455672,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1413},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjzcXeoPUhqL5ruszPqF","type":"assistant","uuid":"c2c46b4b-1040-4bb4-9acb-1824b06032df","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:29:20.066Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"