iles.........................................................Passed\nfix requirements.txt.................................(no files to check)Skipped\nmixed line ending........................................................Passed\ndon't commit to branch...................................................Passed\nLint js with yarn....................................(no files to check)Skipped\nBuild with yarn......................................(no files to check)Skipped\nyamllint.............................................(no files to check)Skipped\nmarkdownlint.........................................(no files to check)Skipped\nflake8...................................................................Passed\nmypy.....................................................................Passed\nLint GitHub Actions workflow files...................(no files to check)Skipped\n[fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling a7fdd4c] Handle Matter duplicate credential rejection as DuplicateCodeError\n 2 files changed, 40 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)\n[entire] Pushing entire/checkpoints/v1 to origin... done\nremote: \nremote: Create a pull request for 'fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling' on GitHub by visiting:        \nremote:      https://github.com/raman325/lock_code_manager/pull/new/fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling        \nremote: \nTo https://github.com/raman325/lock_code_manager.git\n * [new branch]      fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling -> fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling\nbranch 'fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling' set up to track 'origin/fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling'.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6102d8ec-2556-4af0-a6ef-31fc2cde6210","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"type":"queue-operation","operation":"enqueue","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:32:14.020Z","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","content":"this is for matter. And maybe we do want to bypass the service calls if we can get better error handling"}
{"parentUuid":"86f58cd6-d833-4d22-8011-98138f9d2db8","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HiQtwgzL4jNibKFLrSsnKT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VpLVtf5phbcrGJx2MH1aKX","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gh pr create --title \"Handle Matter duplicate credential rejection as DuplicateCodeError\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Proposed change\n\nWhen the Matter lock returns a \"duplicate\" status on `set_lock_credential`, the PIN value already exists on another slot on the lock. This PR detects the duplicate status in the error message and raises `DuplicateCodeError` instead of `LockDisconnected`, so the sync manager can properly disable the slot and notify the user via a repair issue.\n\nThis matches the existing Z-Wave event 15 duplicate code handling flow.\n\n### Root cause\n\nReported in #984: an Aqara U200 user had PINs set on the lock before configuring LCM. When LCM tried to set the same PIN on a managed slot, the lock rejected it with \"duplicate\" status. Previously this was treated as a generic `LockDisconnected` error, causing infinite retry loops.\n\n### Changes\n\n- `async_set_usercode` now catches `LockDisconnected` and checks for \"duplicate\" in the error message\n- When detected, raises `DuplicateCodeError` with the code slot and lock entity ID\n- The sync manager's existing `CodeRejectedError` handling disables the slot and creates a repair issue\n\n## Type of change\n\n- [ ] Dependency upgrade\n- [x] Bugfix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)\n- [ ] New feature (which adds functionality)\n- [ ] Breaking change (fix/feature causing existing functionality to break)\n- [ ] Code quality improvements to existing code or addition of tests\n\n## Additional information\n\n- This PR fixes or closes issue: related to #984\n- 550 tests pass (1 new), all pre-commit hooks pass\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create PR"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1037,"cache_read_input_tokens":462857,"output_tokens":492,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1037,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjzqPHdFLNPSYneEj2ib","type":"assistant","uuid":"7fe0185a-a2f4-412c-94d6-8d5902e4eb1b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:32:15.406Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
