{"parentUuid":"aca25635-f25d-4dac-a1a7-a6a7040fd31f","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JJjjyax2Z6QaZYdauj4QZ3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good point. If we call the Matter server directly (bypassing HA services), we'd get the raw `SetCredentialResponse` with the structured `DlStatus` enum — no string matching needed. We could check `response.status == DlStatus.kDuplicate` directly.\n\nWe already have `_get_matter_client()` which gives us the `MatterClient`. The client has `send_device_command()` which returns the raw response object. This would let us:\n\n1. Get structured error handling (duplicate, occupied, resource exhausted, etc.)\n2. Avoid the HA service layer overhead\n3. Match the pattern of `_get_matter_client()` / `_matter_node_id` we already use for events\n\nThe trade-off is coupling more tightly to the Matter server API instead of going through HA services. But we're already coupled via the event subscription.\n\nWant me to explore this as a follow-up? It would be a bigger refactor — replacing all `_async_call_service` calls with direct Matter client commands. Or we could do it incrementally, starting with just `set_lock_credential` to get the structured duplicate handling."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":635,"cache_read_input_tokens":463894,"output_tokens":264,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":635,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjzrYFALfWuUFVGHJbgE","type":"assistant","uuid":"a6aa19e3-c8b8-4ae7-be77-f4a8d3b6a331","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:32:29.302Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"fix/matter-duplicate-code-handling","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
