{"parentUuid":"14c6f31f-fc12-46cb-9914-eec45a3b23ae","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"4e40bf0b-dda0-407c-b4ce-ad307e81110d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NcgWGvSNnzS26Ygv7eyLdY","type":"tool_result","content":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\nGood morning! Here are some answers for you:\n\n**1. Push subscription failing (\"Matter client or node ID unavailable\")**\n\n1. There is no device_id in the attributes for lock.door_to_garage or lock.cold_storage_room (both aqara U200 locks, the only locks I have by the way). \n\n<img width=\"2280\" height=\"348\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8ae3d4b2-5166-499a-8557-0dc5ade6fbcb\" />\n\n2. Template result is: device_id: NOT SET ; entity_id: lock.door_to_garage\n\n<img width=\"2288\" height=\"307\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/aa1d143b-8530-47eb-88aa-40272cca8d26\" />\n\n3. Settings → Devices → find the Door to Garage lock → identifiers (another screenshot). Node ID is 13 (the network name looks strange, I wonder if that's normal. I haven't really been concerned because the locks work perfectly):\n\n<img width=\"324\" height=\"783\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/53fb941b-4b6f-4349-99a8-23a0a217ec05\" />\n\n4. I've attached the diagnostics file (forgive me, there is a bunch of stuff that chatGPT suggested I redact, let me know if I've redacted something you absolutely need to see)\n\n[Diagnostics (redacted).rtf](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/26487830/Diagnostics.redacted.rtf)\n\n\n**2. \"duplicate\" status on set_lock_credential**\n\nClearing codes does not appear anywhere in the logs. Here is another log file - where I'm toggling the 'enabled' button on the dashboard several times:\n\n[home-assistant_2026-04-05T11-04-30.403Z.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/26487914/home-assistant_2026-04-05T11-04-30.403Z.log)","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"ebe7148e-a750-4cfe-a209-29b1caa9e8d9","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:02:53.579Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\nGood morning! Here are some answers for you:\n\n**1. Push subscription failing (\"Matter client or node ID unavailable\")**\n\n1. There is no device_id in the attributes for lock.door_to_garage or lock.cold_storage_room (both aqara U200 locks, the only locks I have by the way). \n\n<img width=\"2280\" height=\"348\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8ae3d4b2-5166-499a-8557-0dc5ade6fbcb\" />\n\n2. Template result is: device_id: NOT SET ; entity_id: lock.door_to_garage\n\n<img width=\"2288\" height=\"307\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/aa1d143b-8530-47eb-88aa-40272cca8d26\" />\n\n3. Settings → Devices → find the Door to Garage lock → identifiers (another screenshot). Node ID is 13 (the network name looks strange, I wonder if that's normal. I haven't really been concerned because the locks work perfectly):\n\n<img width=\"324\" height=\"783\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/53fb941b-4b6f-4349-99a8-23a0a217ec05\" />\n\n4. I've attached the diagnostics file (forgive me, there is a bunch of stuff that chatGPT suggested I redact, let me know if I've redacted something you absolutely need to see)\n\n[Diagnostics (redacted).rtf](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/26487830/Diagnostics.redacted.rtf)\n\n\n**2. \"duplicate\" status on set_lock_credential**\n\nClearing codes does not appear anywhere in the logs. Here is another log file - where I'm toggling the 'enabled' button on the dashboard several times:\n\n[home-assistant_2026-04-05T11-04-30.403Z.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/26487914/home-assistant_2026-04-05T11-04-30.403Z.log)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"14c6f31f-fc12-46cb-9914-eec45a3b23ae","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"ebe7148e-a750-4cfe-a209-29b1caa9e8d9","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017CkUJMeHM8t1BEJ7XXSxJy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key findings:\n\n1. **`device_id` is NOT SET** on the lock entity — this is why `_matter_node_id` returns None. The entity registry entry has no `device_id`, so `__post_init__` can't resolve the device and we can't find Matter identifiers. This explains both the push subscription failure AND the event entity being unavailable.\n\n2. **Node ID is 13** — visible in the device page but not linked to the entity.\n\n3. **No clearing in logs** — when toggling enabled off, no clear operations appear. This likely means the sync manager isn't detecting the state change, or the clear is failing silently before logging.\n\nThe `device_id` issue is the root cause. Let me check how entity registry entries get their device_id:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":668,"cache_read_input_tokens":472502,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":668},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZkfntWVcxq8hdySFCZ88","type":"assistant","uuid":"a468f365-0003-4c64-b419-149b0c354566","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:03:04.296Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
