{"parentUuid":"1f50d9a2-0a23-4578-b781-c38c9954e4cd","isSidechain":false,"type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Grep","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01GzhYwydDemQ2T5YPmP1DrB","toolUseID":"toolu_01GzhYwydDemQ2T5YPmP1DrB","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:03:06.039Z","uuid":"874f0dbe-42bf-4590-afab-0cae553c1a13","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"1f50d9a2-0a23-4578-b781-c38c9954e4cd","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"4e40bf0b-dda0-407c-b4ce-ad307e81110d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GzhYwydDemQ2T5YPmP1DrB","type":"tool_result","content":"245:        if not (device_id := self.lock.device_id):\n247:        self.device_entry = self.dev_reg.async_get(device_id)\n953:        lock_device_id = self.lock.device_id\n984:            ATTR_DEVICE_ID: lock_device_id,\n\n[Showing results with pagination = limit: 10, offset: 0]"}]},"uuid":"ba2857e9-7384-4bcd-9202-91106c4f5ae6","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:03:06.039Z","toolUseResult":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"245:        if not (device_id := self.lock.device_id):\n247:        self.device_entry = self.dev_reg.async_get(device_id)\n953:        lock_device_id = self.lock.device_id\n984:            ATTR_DEVICE_ID: lock_device_id,","numLines":4,"appliedLimit":10},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1f50d9a2-0a23-4578-b781-c38c9954e4cd","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"ba2857e9-7384-4bcd-9202-91106c4f5ae6","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FvwmWPAPf7yPkFXdwNvDBB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`self.lock` is an `er.RegistryEntry` — its `device_id` field links to the device registry. If the Matter integration didn't set `device_id` when registering the entity, it would be None. This is unusual — most integrations link entities to devices. \n\nBut the device exists (the user can see it in Settings → Devices). It's possible the entity was created before the device was registered, or the Matter integration has a bug where lock entities aren't linked to devices.\n\nLet me draft a response:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":445,"cache_read_input_tokens":473170,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":445},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZkfopGnNmn4vEYqdHMda","type":"assistant","uuid":"ef89d6d9-cbdf-4a49-ae69-dff0a1ac0fd4","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:03:15.994Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"ef89d6d9-cbdf-4a49-ae69-dff0a1ac0fd4","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FvwmWPAPf7yPkFXdwNvDBB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01H4ApVNDUEu7evmnNFvcSw2","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gh issue comment 984 --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nThanks for the detailed diagnostics!\n\n**Root cause found: lock entity has no `device_id`**\n\nThe lock entity (`lock.door_to_garage`) is not linked to its device in the entity registry. This is why:\n- Push subscription fails (can't resolve Matter node ID from device identifiers)\n- Event entity stays unavailable\n- The lock provider can't find the device to subscribe to events\n\nThe device itself exists (node 13, visible in Settings → Devices), but the entity registry entry doesn't have the `device_id` field set. This is unusual — the Matter integration should link the lock entity to its device when creating it.\n\n**Possible fixes:**\n1. Try removing and re-adding the Matter integration — this would re-create the entities with proper device links\n2. If that doesn't work, this may be a bug in the Matter integration's entity registration for lock entities on the Aqara U200\n\n**For the \"duplicate\" error:**\nWe just shipped a fix in the latest release that detects the \"duplicate\" status from the lock and properly surfaces it as a repair issue instead of retrying forever. The duplicate means the same PIN value already exists on another slot on the lock. You'll need to clear those conflicting codes — once the lock reset step (PR #983) ships, it will offer to do this during setup.\n\n**For the missing clear operations:**\nThe logs showing only `set` operations (not `clear`) when you disable a slot is concerning. Can you check: when you toggle the enabled switch off, does the active binary sensor go to OFF? If so, the sync manager should attempt a clear on the next tick. The logs should show `Clearing usercode on lock.door_to_garage slot N`. If that message is completely absent, there may be a sync manager issue separate from the device_id problem.\n\n**Immediate workaround:**\nTry reloading the Matter integration (Settings → Integrations → Matter → 3 dots → Reload). After reload, check if `device_id` appears on the lock entity in Developer Tools → States.\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Comment on 984"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":445,"cache_read_input_tokens":473170,"output_tokens":671,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":445,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZkfopGnNmn4vEYqdHMda","type":"assistant","uuid":"24c7089c-10f8-4071-8624-a35511abdd38","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:03:29.024Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"24c7089c-10f8-4071-8624-a35511abdd38","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"4e40bf0b-dda0-407c-b4ce-ad307e81110d","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H4ApVNDUEu7evmnNFvcSw2","type":"tool_result","content":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\nhttps://github.com/raman325/lock_code_manager/issues/984#issuecomment-4188861057","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"4f8c33e4-9851-4986-b33a-39810aa5f644","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:03:30.674Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\nhttps://github.com/raman325/lock_code_manager/issues/984#issuecomment-4188861057","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"24c7089c-10f8-4071-8624-a35511abdd38","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"4f8c33e4-9851-4986-b33a-39810aa5f644","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MMmsTV8uTt4Q4gY4ZZaGKA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The missing `device_id` is the root cause for all three issues. Without it, the Matter provider can't resolve the node ID for event subscriptions or find the device entry for identifiers. The lock entity exists but isn't linked to its device in the entity registry — likely a Matter integration issue with how the Aqara U200 entities were registered."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":863,"cache_read_input_tokens":473615,"output_tokens":79,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":863,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZkfqdEZiavMZG1xbqvzy","type":"assistant","uuid":"5f8d701e-c96b-4098-aedd-9788973ca762","timestamp":"2026-04-05T13:03:39.330Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
