{"parentUuid":"2ff1aad9-e8cd-4d60-9b79-3fe473bcc9c1","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"6628f9a5-21b2-4d3f-ac0a-511ee1ee8b8a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018qn6CPxPX1Q7mBxGwiwRpT","type":"tool_result","content":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\nDeleted branch fix/enhance-device-id-warning (was 720963a).","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"98f5a14a-6b72-4c9c-a3d4-e7f34d7c4f5b","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:13:34.742Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"/Users/raman/.claude/shell-snapshots/snapshot-bash-1775143734045-fw9p9j.sh: line 372: alias: --: not found\nDeleted branch fix/enhance-device-id-warning (was 720963a).","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2ff1aad9-e8cd-4d60-9b79-3fe473bcc9c1","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"98f5a14a-6b72-4c9c-a3d4-e7f34d7c4f5b","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01U1QeUoWkB7d1G5MqGGkJbg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Great, main is up to date. What lock did you get? That'll help me tailor the commissioning steps — some Matter locks have quirks around pairing mode and credential setup.\n\nHere's the general walkthrough:\n\n## Step 1: Commission the lock via HA\n\n1. Put the lock into pairing/commissioning mode (usually a button sequence on the lock — check the manual)\n2. In HA: **Settings → Devices & Services → Add Integration → Matter**\n   - If Matter is already set up, go to **Matter integration → Add Device**\n3. Enter the Matter pairing code (numeric code from the lock's QR code or manual)\n4. Wait for commissioning to complete — the lock should appear as a device with a `lock.*` entity\n\n**Verify after commissioning:**\n- Settings → Devices → find the lock → confirm it shows Matter identifiers (node ID)\n- Developer Tools → States → search for the lock entity → confirm `device_id` is set (this was the issue #984 user hit)\n\n## Step 2: Set up in LCM\n\n1. **Settings → Devices & Services → Add Integration → Lock Code Manager**\n2. Give it a name, select your Matter lock\n3. You'll go through the config flow — if the lock has existing codes, you should see the lock reset step (PR #983 when merged)\n4. Choose UI or YAML path, configure slots with PINs\n\n## Step 3: Testing scenarios\n\nOnce set up, here's what we should test:\n\n| Scenario | What to check |\n|----------|--------------|\n| Set PIN | Code sensor shows configured PIN, in-sync goes on |\n| Disable slot | Active goes off, PIN is cleared on lock |\n| Re-enable slot | PIN is re-set, in-sync goes on |\n| Use PIN at keypad | Event entity fires `pin_used` |\n| External PIN change | LockUserChange event detected, coordinator updates |\n| Duplicate PIN | DuplicateCodeError, slot disabled with repair issue |\n| Lock offline | After 12 poll failures, `lock_offline` repair issue |\n\nWhat lock did you get? And is the Matter integration already set up in your HA instance?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":160,"cache_read_input_tokens":486886,"output_tokens":505,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":160,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZo8SeAtA3HdvKdrHbddt","type":"assistant","uuid":"64a0a9ea-ec0f-46ba-afec-ee45715e0f8b","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:13:56.207Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
