{"parentUuid":"376c8499-08fa-4b23-a374-2091419469c7","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"8f0122a2-17f0-4812-9a03-d383e2cb5a56","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"first, I am getting \"Failed to save thread network credential error: Thread network credentials does not match with anyo f the active thread networks around\""},"uuid":"1476e1d3-182f-4c91-ae0f-7333444c2400","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:16:16.288Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"1476e1d3-182f-4c91-ae0f-7333444c2400","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01P3TY7AecoSUK5thmWihegk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThat's a Thread commissioning error — the lock is a Thread-based Matter device (most Matter locks are). The error means HA's Matter integration is trying to push Thread network credentials to the lock, but the lock can't find a matching Thread network to join.\n\nA few things to check:\n\n**Do you have a Thread border router?**\nMatter over Thread requires a border router. Common options:\n- Apple HomePod Mini / Apple TV 4K (if you have one on the network)\n- Google Nest Hub (2nd gen) / Nest Wifi Pro\n- Home Assistant SkyConnect or Yellow with the Thread firmware\n- Any OpenThread Border Router\n\nCheck: **Settings → Integrations → Thread** — do you see any border routers listed?\n\n**If you have a border router:**\nThe lock might be too far from the border router during commissioning. Thread is mesh but the initial join needs to reach a border router directly. Try:\n1. Move the lock closer to the border router for initial commissioning\n2. Make sure the border router is powered on and active\n\n**If you don't have a border router:**\nYou'll need one. The cheapest path is a SkyConnect USB stick ($30) flashed with the Thread/Matter firmware plugged into your HA host.\n\n**Alternative: Commission via another controller first**\nIf you have an Apple Home or Google Home setup with Thread, you can commission the lock there first, then share it to HA via multi-admin. But for testing LCM, direct HA commissioning is cleaner.\n\nWhat's your Thread setup look like?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":536,"cache_read_input_tokens":487046,"output_tokens":355,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":536,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZo8f99juF8niDTaBPnn4","type":"assistant","uuid":"5d480523-e137-4aab-b8d8-4e65efaca122","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:16:39.707Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
