{"parentUuid":"236f1d9b-382a-4d48-9c4f-008a2f377858","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"6bd3b80e-2f37-4d04-abb0-0a778fe08567","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"now I am getting \"Thread Border Router\" required, but I have one setup in HA OS an conmfigured in core. Thread looks fine too"},"uuid":"12cf8d52-7d4e-49b1-98e6-80361de203b1","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:21:06.120Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"12cf8d52-7d4e-49b1-98e6-80361de203b1","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WFBU9QXfh7dBq4UuWZN6wb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nCould be that the Matter integration isn't picking up the Thread credentials from HA. A few things:\n\n1. **Check Thread credential sync**: Settings → Integrations → Thread — does it show \"Preferred network\" with credentials? The Matter integration needs to pull credentials from the Thread integration.\n\n2. **Check Matter → Thread linkage**: Settings → Integrations → Matter → Configure — is there an option to select the Thread network or sync credentials?\n\n3. **Restart order matters**: Sometimes the Matter integration needs to be reloaded after Thread is configured. Try:\n   - Settings → Integrations → Matter → 3 dots → Reload\n   - Then try adding the device again\n\n4. **HA OS multiprotocol**: If you're using the SkyConnect or similar with multiprotocol (Zigbee + Thread on the same stick), make sure multiprotocol is enabled in the add-on settings and both radios are active.\n\n5. **Check the Matter server logs**: Enable debug logging for Matter:\n```yaml\nlogger:\n  logs:\n    homeassistant.components.matter: debug\n    matter_server: debug\n```\nThen try commissioning again — the logs should show what Thread network it's trying to use and why it fails.\n\nWhat border router hardware are you using? And how did you set up Thread — via the SkyConnect add-on, or another way?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391,"cache_read_input_tokens":487582,"output_tokens":314,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":391,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZo92FUaYeop9wkB7otVH","type":"assistant","uuid":"9610f02a-9251-4041-bf03-6b61b657d125","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:21:25.294Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
