{"parentUuid":"8cf10d31-092d-4195-a3aa-1444405243b5","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"f61a2272-071c-4750-a918-c5a2e7b56fa9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"what do I set thread credentials to? I am using a ZBT-2 without multiprotocol"},"uuid":"3942b23d-0c38-4e85-ac32-3bf4ea92ce97","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:23:49.761Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"3942b23d-0c38-4e85-ac32-3bf4ea92ce97","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017gBfq1MZtSAHrM8QDGJBrX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nWithout multiprotocol, the ZBT-2 is running either Zigbee OR Thread, not both. \n\n**Check which firmware is on the ZBT-2:**\nSettings → System → Hardware → ZBT-2 (or check the Silicon Labs Multiprotocol / Zigbee add-on)\n\nIf it's running Zigbee firmware, it can't be a Thread border router at the same time. You'd need a separate Thread border router.\n\n**Options:**\n\n1. **Switch the ZBT-2 to Thread firmware** — but then you lose Zigbee. Only do this if you don't have Zigbee devices.\n\n2. **Use a second radio for Thread** — a SkyConnect stick ($30) or another ZBT-2, one for Zigbee and one for Thread.\n\n3. **Use an existing Thread border router** — if you have an Apple HomePod Mini, Apple TV 4K, Google Nest Hub 2nd gen, or Nest Wifi Pro on your network, they act as Thread border routers. HA can discover them automatically via the Thread integration.\n\n**What Thread border router did you think you had set up?** If you go to Settings → Integrations → Thread, what does it show? It might be discovering a border router from another ecosystem (Apple/Google) on your network but not having credentials synced.\n\nFor your Matter lock to commission, you need an active Thread border router that HA's Matter integration can pass credentials from. The \"Thread credentials\" in the Matter commissioning flow should auto-populate from the Thread integration — if it's asking you to set them manually, it means it can't find a usable Thread network."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":340,"cache_read_input_tokens":487973,"output_tokens":386,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":340,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZo9ER95irhwY4NgEs7EH","type":"assistant","uuid":"c7e160fb-2a6a-4170-9ef6-b621162d07d8","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:24:11.878Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
