{"parentUuid":"54d29926-d643-46e5-8a99-7b45c342d4d0","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"255e4442-80e5-483b-9be6-1d9b8a4649e4","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"I just migrated to Thread, not sure if it did anything"},"uuid":"04545b6c-fb0a-497d-9418-eb30a93137e7","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:25:37.421Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"04545b6c-fb0a-497d-9418-eb30a93137e7","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017Czc5Wz3Na1cryJ3mjftox","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOK so the ZBT-2 should now be a Thread border router. Let me help you verify it's actually working:\n\n**1. Check Thread integration status:**\n- Settings → Integrations → **Thread**\n- Click into it — you should see your border router listed (something like \"Home Assistant\" or the ZBT-2 hostname)\n- Click the border router → it should show:\n  - **Active dataset** (with network name, channel, PAN ID)\n  - **Border agent** status\n\n**2. If there's no active dataset:**\nThe Thread network needs to be created. Click the border router and look for \"Set as preferred\" or \"Create network\" option.\n\n**3. Check the Silicon Labs Multiprotocol or OTBR add-on:**\n- Settings → Add-ons → look for **OpenThread Border Router** or **Silicon Labs Multiprotocol**\n- Make sure it's running (green dot)\n- Check its logs for any errors\n\n**4. After Thread is healthy, reload Matter:**\n- Settings → Integrations → Matter → 3 dots → **Reload**\n- This forces Matter to re-read Thread credentials\n\n**5. Try commissioning again:**\nThe error you got was \"Thread network credentials does not match with any of the active thread networks around\" — this means either:\n- The lock is too far from the border router (try commissioning right next to the ZBT-2)\n- The Thread network isn't actually formed/active yet\n- The credentials HA is sending don't match what the border router is broadcasting\n\nWhat do you see in Settings → Integrations → Thread now? Does it show an active dataset for your border router?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":642442,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":642442},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZo9NH1ub7e1KbiXwoDNw","type":"assistant","uuid":"4ef46e5f-3b3b-4181-b6fa-d04786183468","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:26:05.992Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
