{"parentUuid":"719f9b3c-d598-4ccb-a1d9-018d99416bd5","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EV5xUz62wry712HeSXULN8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThat looks healthy — Thread network is active on channel 15. Now let me figure out why Matter still can't commission.\n\n**Try these in order:**\n\n1. **Reload Matter integration**\n   - Settings → Integrations → Matter → 3 dots → Reload\n   - This forces it to pull the latest Thread credentials\n\n2. **Move the lock right next to the ZBT-2**\n   - Within a few feet during commissioning\n   - The \"credentials does not match active networks around\" error often means the lock can't hear the Thread network's beacons because of distance/interference\n\n3. **Make sure the lock is actually in pairing mode**\n   - Most Matter locks need to be factory reset or have pairing explicitly triggered\n   - The lock should be advertising itself for commissioning (often indicated by an LED pattern)\n\n4. **Try commissioning again**\n   - Settings → Devices & Services → Matter → Add Device\n   - Scan QR code or enter the manual pairing code\n\n**If it still fails:**\n\nEnable Matter debug logging temporarily:\n```yaml\nlogger:\n  logs:\n    homeassistant.components.matter: debug\n    matter_server: debug\n```\n\nRestart HA, try commissioning, then share the relevant log section. The Matter server should log:\n- What Thread credentials it's sending (should match channel 15, PAN 32dc, extended PAN fce57ef57e2593cd)\n- The lock's response and where it fails\n\nWhat lock are you trying to commission? Some have specific pairing quirks."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":757,"cache_read_input_tokens":642442,"output_tokens":495,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":757,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZo9ScmfHkKWFM4r88jhr","type":"assistant","uuid":"c803128d-ffd7-49b9-9687-c284e0f5dff8","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:26:51.348Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
