it done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:35.264 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:35.913 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:37.245 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:37.654 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:37.861 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:38.080 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:38.319 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:38.536 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:38.745 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:38.933 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:00.477 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:11.148 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:20.323 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:36.360 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:49.286 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:02:35.624 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure"},"uuid":"dbcc8f47-1cf3-4452-a63d-418dc84be480","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:28:36.607Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"dbcc8f47-1cf3-4452-a63d-418dc84be480","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JJDF9vaELPRehLNaCfSTWZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOK, I see the actual problem now. The OTBR is forming the network successfully (it became leader), but look at all the `Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure` warnings. **The radio can't transmit** — every time it tries to send a packet on channel 15, the radio reports the channel is busy.\n\nThis is **WiFi interference**. Channel 15 in 2.4GHz IEEE 802.15.4 (Thread/Zigbee) overlaps heavily with WiFi channel 6. The ZBT-2 keeps trying to transmit and the radio detects WiFi traffic on the same frequency, so it backs off and never sends anything.\n\n**Why this matters:** The Thread network is \"active\" (border router thinks it's leader), but it's not actually broadcasting Thread beacons that the lock can hear. So when you try to commission, the lock can't find a Thread network → \"credentials don't match any active network around\" / \"no border router.\"\n\n**The fix: change the Thread channel**\n\nYou need to pick a channel that doesn't overlap with your WiFi:\n\n| Thread/Zigbee | Overlaps with WiFi |\n|---------------|-------------------|\n| 11 | 1-2 |\n| 12-14 | 1-6 |\n| **15** | **6** ← your current channel |\n| 16-19 | 6-11 |\n| 20 | 9-11 |\n| **25** | minimal |\n| **26** | none |\n\n**Best Thread channels: 25 or 26** (clear of WiFi 1-11).\n\n**To change it:**\n\n1. Settings → Integrations → Thread → click your border router\n2. Look for \"Reset network\" or \"Form new network\" option (in newer HA there's a way to reform with a different channel)\n3. Or via the OTBR add-on web UI at the URL it logs (the web UI lets you reform with a chosen channel)\n\n**Alternative:** Move the ZBT-2 physically away from your WiFi router/AP — the interference is worst when they're stacked on top of each other. Even a few feet of separation helps a lot.\n\nOnce Thread is on a clean channel, the `ChannelAccessFailure` warnings should disappear and Matter commissioning should work."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8131,"cache_read_input_tokens":643715,"output_tokens":719,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8131,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZo9bc4Vq62RJWuTrq8EX","type":"assistant","uuid":"b5c119cd-a691-4dab-be51-8b5e09899255","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:28:58.810Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
