{"parentUuid":"262eb74b-5de6-4be4-9840-393456acf842","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"161e9a06-5c21-458a-b244-b29daf08b8e6","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"I actually want to blow my thread network away and start over. How do I do that? I notice the thread key is also the preconfigured one and I'd like to properly set that up"},"uuid":"2abbbacc-e400-4655-aa06-93b636bf21c3","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:34:26.246Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"2abbbacc-e400-4655-aa06-93b636bf21c3","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UTDRauTURXS7vAXriztG9a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood call — the dataset you shared earlier has the Network Key field embedded but using HA's auto-generated default. Wiping and reforming gives you a clean network with a fresh key, and it's a good chance to pick a non-WiFi-overlapping channel.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Delete the existing network from HA:**\n   - Settings → Devices & Services → **Thread**\n   - Click your border router (Home Assistant / OTBR)\n   - 3 dots → **Delete** (this removes it from the Thread integration)\n\n2. **Stop and reset the OTBR add-on:**\n   - Settings → Add-ons → **OpenThread Border Router** → Stop\n   - Then: Settings → Add-ons → **OpenThread Border Router** → 3 dots → **Reset to defaults** (or uninstall + reinstall if there's no reset option). This clears the persisted Thread dataset on the add-on side.\n   - Alternatively, if you have SSH access: delete `/data/thread/*.data` files inside the add-on container\n\n3. **Start the OTBR add-on fresh:**\n   - It will boot with no dataset and won't auto-form a network\n\n4. **Form a new network from HA with your chosen settings:**\n   - Settings → Devices & Services → Thread → your border router (it should re-discover)\n   - Click **Form new network** (or similar)\n   - HA will generate a fresh dataset (new network key, PAN ID, channel)\n\n**For the channel:** HA's \"Form new network\" usually picks an automatic channel based on RF scan. If you want to force channel 25 or 26, you may need to do it via the OTBR web UI directly or by manually setting the Thread dataset via the API.\n\n**Manual channel selection via API:**\n\nYou can call the Thread integration's `set_preferred_dataset_tlv` service with a custom dataset, but the easier path is to use the OTBR web UI:\n- Try opening `http://<ha-ip>:8081` (the OTBR add-on may need port 8081 exposed in its config first)\n- The web UI lets you form a network with a chosen channel and network key\n\n**Alternative: HA Thread has a \"Use this border router as preferred\" flow**\n\nIn recent HA versions (2026.x), the Thread integration has a \"Reform with new credentials\" option that lets you specify a channel. Check Settings → Integrations → Thread → your border router → look for any reform/configure option.\n\nWhat HA version are you on? That'll determine whether the in-UI channel selection is available or if you need to go through the OTBR web UI."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":882,"cache_read_input_tokens":652585,"output_tokens":838,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":882,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZoA3H9S3cZ2DokhSQ7wg","type":"assistant","uuid":"21158450-8166-45ee-b1d6-e49b2644b559","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:34:46.916Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
