{"parentUuid":"78545ade-fcab-4109-ac10-619d45b31b7a","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"e5c530d3-e85b-4546-9cce-14f00f5eb686","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"I created my preferred network, and I can see the OpenThread other network. I can't change the channel on the node, I keep getting the OTBR API error. I have not tried to add it to the preferred network yet but I expect to get the same error"},"uuid":"708516bd-4013-417b-a7cf-8687a9064a2f","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:38:58.987Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"708516bd-4013-417b-a7cf-8687a9064a2f","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XwXDs7Nh2wV4kVVsWKx5p7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOK so HA can form a preferred network but can't push it to the OTBR node — that's the API connectivity issue. The Thread integration calls the OTBR REST API at `http://core-openthread-border-router:8081` and that's failing.\n\nBefore trying to migrate the OTBR node to your preferred network (which will fail the same way), let's fix the API connectivity.\n\n**Check the add-on's network config:**\n\n1. Settings → Add-ons → **OpenThread Border Router** → **Configuration** tab\n2. Look at the Network section. There should be options for:\n   - REST API port (8081)\n   - Whether host networking is enabled\n\n3. Settings → Add-ons → **OpenThread Border Router** → **Info** tab → check the \"Network\" section at the bottom — does it show port 8081 mapped?\n\n**Try exposing the REST API explicitly:**\n- In the Configuration tab, set the REST API port to `8081`\n- Save and restart the add-on\n\n**Test API reachability from HA Core:**\n\nRun this in Developer Tools → Template:\n```jinja\n{{ states('sensor.uptime') }}\n```\nJust to confirm templates work. Then we need a way to curl from HA. Easier: look at HA Core logs after attempting the migration:\n\n1. Settings → System → Logs\n2. Try to migrate the OTBR node to the preferred network in the Thread UI\n3. Watch for the actual error in the logs — there should be a more detailed message than \"Failed to call OTBR API\" (connection refused, name resolution failed, timeout, etc.)\n\n**Most likely cause:**\n\nIn HA OS, supervisor add-ons live on a Docker network and HA Core resolves them via the `core-*` hostnames. If the OTBR add-on is running but Core can't resolve `core-openthread-border-router`, it suggests the add-on slug or hostname has changed, or the Thread integration was set up before the add-on was reinstalled and has cached the wrong URL.\n\n**Try this:**\n1. Settings → Devices & Services → Thread → 3 dots → **Delete** (removes the integration entirely, not just the network)\n2. Restart HA Core (Settings → System → Restart)\n3. After restart, the Thread integration should auto-discover the OTBR add-on and re-add itself with the correct hostname\n\nThen try the migration again. What's the exact error in HA Core logs when the API call fails?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":914,"cache_read_input_tokens":653467,"output_tokens":787,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":914,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZoAPL2dCqeYhJBSB9AAg","type":"assistant","uuid":"625a7d45-9864-4c99-80e7-5666b17e43b6","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:39:19.010Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
