769 [W] DuaManager----: Failed to perform next registration: NotFound\n00:00:45.843 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:46.303 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:46.563 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:49.738 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:53.707 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:54.693 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:00:54.932 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:09.834 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:19.280 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:01:31.656 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:02:05.698 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:02:14.431 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:02:14.664 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure\n00:02:29.883 [W] P-RadioSpinel-: Handle transmit done failed: ChannelAccessFailure"},"uuid":"f78cc3fa-2d35-4625-9eb4-3986538f836f","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:44:52.700Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"f78cc3fa-2d35-4625-9eb4-3986538f836f","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GUUZbMUpcVAcbt3FBX9mx9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nTwo important things from these logs:\n\n**1. The radio is fundamentally broken right now**\n\nThe `ChannelAccessFailure` is happening on EVERY single transmit attempt — dozens per minute. This isn't just \"channel busy occasionally,\" this is the radio literally not being able to send anything. Even after the OTBR reformed and became leader, it can't transmit a single packet.\n\nA few possibilities:\n- **Radio firmware mismatch** — the ZBT-2 might be running old/wrong RCP firmware\n- **Hardware issue** — the radio is failing\n- **USB power issue** — insufficient power to the stick\n- **Antenna issue** — but you said it just got migrated, so unlikely physical\n\n**2. Settings file invalid + version mismatch**\n\n```\nSettings file /data/thread/0_f074bffffe4065e2.data is not a valid OTBR settings file, skipping\n[NOTE]-AGENT---: Thread version: 1.3.0\n```\n\nEarlier logs showed Thread 1.4.0, now it's 1.3.0. The OTBR add-on version may have changed (or rolled back) and the persisted settings file is incompatible. This means even if the radio worked, the dataset migration would fail.\n\nAlso: `Running 0.3.0-b067e5ac-dirty` — the \"-dirty\" suffix means this is a development build, not a release.\n\n**Recommended path forward:**\n\n1. **Check ZBT-2 firmware**:\n   - Settings → Hardware → ZBT-2 (or wherever it's listed)\n   - It should show the RCP firmware version\n   - If you can update to the latest Silicon Labs RCP firmware, do it\n\n2. **Verify the OTBR add-on isn't on a beta channel**:\n   - Settings → Add-ons → OpenThread Border Router → Configuration\n   - Check if \"Beta\" or development version is enabled\n   - If so, switch to stable\n\n3. **The \"-dirty\" build is suspicious** — that should be a clean release build. Try uninstalling the OTBR add-on completely, then reinstalling from the official add-on store.\n\n4. **Test the radio with Zigbee instead** (sanity check): If you flash the ZBT-2 back to Zigbee firmware temporarily, do Zigbee transmissions also fail? If yes, hardware/USB issue. If no, it's a Thread/RCP firmware problem specifically.\n\n**Honest take:** Your Thread setup is in a bad state — invalid settings file, dirty dev build of OTBR, every transmit failing. Rather than fight this, I'd recommend:\n\n1. Stop and **uninstall** the OTBR add-on entirely\n2. Reinstall a clean stable release from the add-on store\n3. Make sure the ZBT-2 has current production RCP firmware\n\nIf after a clean reinstall the `ChannelAccessFailure` errors persist, that's a hardware/firmware problem with the stick that needs Nabu Casa support, not an HA config issue."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6369,"cache_read_input_tokens":654381,"output_tokens":990,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6369,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZoAqbk9mR8iPV3JkHopW","type":"assistant","uuid":"9d86c02e-d34d-4796-a067-674da2735614","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:45:19.372Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
