{"parentUuid":"dc609507-b8ea-4560-81dc-1382716084f2","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"0ad17b69-23d3-4592-b0ba-2863d8922a21","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"now the radio failures are gone but I am still getting the no border routers detected failure"},"uuid":"41bfc6ce-616b-4e5a-846d-95d241115a07","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:55:18.778Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"41bfc6ce-616b-4e5a-846d-95d241115a07","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PzX4e9VLuACvunNTh1MWK5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood — clean reinstall fixed the radio. Now the next layer: Matter can't see the OTBR.\n\n**Verify the OTBR is actually working first:**\n- Settings → Devices & Services → **Thread** → click your border router\n- It should show:\n  - Network name, channel, PAN ID, etc.\n  - \"Border agent\" or \"active\" status\n  - Recent activity (no `ChannelAccessFailure` in OTBR logs anymore?)\n\n**Check the Matter ↔ Thread linkage:**\n\nThe Matter integration discovers Thread border routers via mDNS (`_meshcop._udp.local`). Even though the Thread integration in HA can talk to the OTBR via the supervisor network, the **Matter server** is a separate process that needs to discover the border router via mDNS on the LAN.\n\n**Things to check:**\n\n1. **Is the OTBR add-on advertising via mDNS?**\n   - Earlier logs said: `Beta mode enabled, using OpenThread built-in mDNS`\n   - Make sure that's still set, OR that the add-on uses the supervisor's mDNS forwarder\n   - Check OTBR add-on Configuration tab — there should be an mDNS-related option\n\n2. **Network mode of the OTBR add-on:**\n   - Settings → Add-ons → OpenThread Border Router → Configuration → Network section\n   - For mDNS to reach the LAN, the add-on needs **host networking** OR the supervisor needs to forward mDNS traffic\n   - Check if there's a \"host network\" toggle\n\n3. **Restart the Matter add-on/integration:**\n   - Settings → Add-ons → Matter Server → Restart\n   - Then: Settings → Integrations → Matter → 3 dots → Reload\n   - This forces Matter to re-scan for border routers\n\n4. **Verify mDNS visibility:**\n   - If you have a way to scan mDNS from another device on your network (e.g., `dns-sd -B _meshcop._udp` on macOS, or `avahi-browse -a` on Linux), check whether the OTBR is being advertised\n   - You should see something like `<network-name>._meshcop._udp.local`\n\n5. **Check Matter server logs for border router discovery:**\n   ```yaml\n   logger:\n     logs:\n       matter_server: debug\n   ```\n   - Restart, then watch for log lines about discovering border routers or Thread datasets\n   - There should be messages like \"Found border router\" or \"No border routers found\"\n\n**Most likely fix:** The OTBR add-on needs host networking enabled for its mDNS broadcasts to reach the Matter server. Check the add-on's Configuration tab for that option.\n\nWhat does Settings → Devices & Services → Thread show for the border router status now?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1020,"cache_read_input_tokens":660750,"output_tokens":908,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1020,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZoBdmaH6H6x4K8nDUhWq","type":"assistant","uuid":"a595c06a-8e21-4892-a129-7db38e6355fb","timestamp":"2026-04-06T20:55:44.723Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
